Scientists at Massachusetts Institute of Technology believe the first complex conversation took place around 50,000 to 100,000 years ago . 
  Much of it involved cavemen grunting, or hunter-gatherers mumbling and pointing . 
  Linguist Shigeru Miyagawa says human language developed rapidly . 
  He says the hierarchical complexity found in present-day language is likely to have been present in human language since its emergence . 
  Most scholars believe humans first started using a 'proto-language'